\n          \"title\": \"Dual Claude Max Accounts — claude2 Is Intentional\",\n          \"importanceTier\": \"constitutional\",\n          \"retrieval_directive\": \"Always surface when: rule applies — must authenticate via the env-var OAuth token to coexist without clobbering account #1's Keychain login. | Prioritize when: Do not treat the second config dir as an error.\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": 9,\n          \"specFolder\": \"system-spec-kit\",\n          \"filePath\": \"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/constitutional/comment-hygiene.md\",\n          \"title\": \"Comment Hygiene — No Ephemeral Artifact Pointers in Code Comments\",\n          \"importanceTier\": \"constitutional\",\n          \"retrieval_directive\": \"Always surface when: rule applies — must be caught | Prioritize when: Never embed spec-folder paths, packet/phase numbers, ADR ids, task/checklist/requirement ids, or finding ids in code co…\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": 8,\n          \"specFolder\": \"system-spec-kit\",\n          \"filePath\": \"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/constitutional/codex-cli-auth-usable.md\",\n          \"title\": \"Codex CLI — Auth Is Usable, Skip the Pre-Flight ASK\",\n          \"importanceTier\": \"constitutional\",\n          \"retrieval_directive\": \"Always surface when: the cli-codex auth pre-flight, and do NOT ask the user to configure auth. | Prioritize when: a real dispatch returns an auth error mid-run should you re-check — and use `codex login` / `codex doctor` (valid subco…\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"triggered\": [\n        {\n          \"memory_id\": 8301,\n          \"spec_folder\": \"system-spec-kit/z_archive/024-compact-code-graph\",\n          \"title\": \"Deep Research Report: Compact Code Graph — Complete Findings [system-spec-kit/024-compact-code-graph/research]\",\n          \"matc