{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780373660000,"sessionID":"ses_1797707a9ffehSuq7kNyovejK9","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_7E5XXydWpfsk1GL7VsdbeD7m","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/benchmark/README.md","offset":1,"limit":130},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/benchmark/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"sk-code Skill-Benchmark Artifacts\"\n3: description: \"Benchmark inputs and reports for sk-code, scored by the deep-improvement Lane C harness in router and live modes.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"sk-code benchmark\"\n6:   - \"skill-benchmark artifacts\"\n7:   - \"sk-code routing benchmark\"\n8: ---\n9: \n10: # sk-code Skill-Benchmark Artifacts\n11: \n12: > Reports and inputs for benchmarking how well `sk-code` is routed, discovered, and used in practice, kept beside the skill they measure.\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n17: \n18: The deep-improvement Lane C harness benchmarks `sk-code` against its own `manual_testing_playbook` scenarios across five dimensions (D1 routing, D2 discovery, D3 efficiency, D4 usefulness, D5 connectivity). This folder holds the run inputs and the dual reports each run writes.\n19: \n20: Two trace modes score the same playbook corpus:\n21: \n22: - **router** is deterministic and offline. It replays the machine-readable router in `sk-code/references/smart_routing.md`. This is the CI gate.\n23: - **live** dispatches each scenario through `cli-opencode` to a real model and grades the model's stated routing plus observed activation. This is the operator default for a true routing verdict.\n24: \n25: ### Key Statistics\n26: \n27: | Metric | Value |\n28: |---|---|\n29: | Corpus | sk-code `manual_testing_playbook` (24 scenarios: 15 routing, 2 advisor, 7 browser) |\n30: | Trace modes | router (deterministic CI gate), live (real dispatch) |\n31: | Latest router verdict | FAIL, aggregate 40 |\n32: | Latest live verdict | CONDITIONAL, aggregate 71 |\n33: | D4 usefulness (approximate) | about 49 |\n34: \n35: ### How This Compares\n36: \n37: | Tool | Checks | Use When |\n38: |---|---|---|\n39: | This benchmark | Whether the skill is routed, discovered, and useful in practice | Measuring real routing quality |\n40: | `validate.sh` | Document shape and required sections | Checking spec-folder structure |\n41: | `manual_testing_playbook` | Described behavior per scenario | Authoring or hand-running scenarios |\n42: \n43: ---\n44: \n45: ## 2. QUICK START\n46: \n47: Run from the repository root.\n48: \n49: Router mode (deterministic, no network):\n50: \n51: ```bash\n52: node .opencode/skills/deep-improvement/scripts/shared/loop-host.cjs \\\n53:   --mode=skill-benchmark --skill=sk-code \\\n54:   --outputs-dir=.opencode/skills/sk-code/benchmark/router-final \\\n55:   --trace-mode=router\n56: ```\n57: \n58: Live mode (dispatches through cli-opencode, needs a configured provider):\n59: \n60: ```bash\n61: SKILL_BENCH_OPENCODE_MODEL=openai/gpt-5.5-fast SKILL_BENCH_OPENCODE_VARIANT=high \\\n62: node .opencode/skills/deep-improvement/scripts/shared/loop-host.cjs \\\n63:   --mode=skill-benchmark --skill=sk-code \\\n64:   --outputs-dir=.opencode/skills/sk-code/benchmark/live-final \\\n65:   --trace-mode=live --advisor-mode=python \\\n66:   --scenarios=SD-001,LS-001,CS-001,RD-002,MR-001\n67: ```\n68: \n69: Expected result: a `verdict=` line on stdout plus `skill-benchmark-report.json` and `skill-benchmark-report.md` in the outputs dir.\n70: \n71: ---\n72: \n73: ## 3. STRUCTURE\n74: \n75: ```text\n76: benchmark/\n77: +-- router-final/      # Current deterministic run (router mode)\n78: +-- live-final/        # Current live run (cli-opencode) + d4-ablation.json\n79: +-- baseline/          # Frozen pre-optimization snapshot, do not regenerate\n80: +-- after/ full/ live/ # Earlier development runs, superseded by the -final pair\n81: `-- fixtures/sk-code/   # Legacy synthetic fixtures, superseded by the playbook corpus\n82: ```\n83: \n84: | Path | Purpose |\n85: |---|---|\n86: | `router-final/` | Latest router-mode report (real-gold scoring, the CI gate) |\n87: | `live-final/` | Latest live-mode report plus `d4-ablation.json` (skill-on vs skill-off usefulness) |\n88: | `baseline/` | First sk-code run, kept as a before-snapshot, not reproducible |\n89: | `fixtures/sk-code/` | Two legacy fixtures, no longer the default corpus |\n90: \n91: ---\n92: \n93: ## 4. READING THE REPORTS\n94: \n95: Each run writes a matched pair:\n96: \n97: | File | Content |\n98: |---|---|\n99: | `skill-benchmark-report.json` | Machine report: verdict, D1 to D5, funnel, ranked bottlenecks, scenario rows |\n100: | `skill-benchmark-report.md` | The same report rendered for reading, generated from the JSON to avoid drift |\n101: | `d4-ablation.json` | Usefulness deltas per scenario (skill-on score, skill-off score), stamped approximate |\n102: \n103: Start with the `.md` file for the verdict and the ranked bottlenecks. Open the `.json` file for per-scenario detail.\n104: \n105: ---\n106: \n107: ## 5. TROUBLESHOOTING\n108: \n109: | What you see | Cause | Fix |\n110: |---|---|---|\n111: | Live dispatch returns null after about 4 minutes | `xhigh` reasoning variant is too slow per dispatch | Set `SKILL_BENCH_OPENCODE_VARIANT=high` |\n112: | `provider/model not found` or 401 in live mode | The provider is not configured | Run `opencode providers list`, then log in to the provider you name in `SKILL_BENCH_OPENCODE_MODEL` |\n113: | Browser scenarios skip with `SKIP-NO-BROWSER` | `bdg` (Chrome) is unavailable | Install `bdg`, or accept the honest skip for non-Chrome legs |\n114: | Router mode reports orphan references | A routable doc is not reachable from the router | Add it to `RESOURCE_MAP` or the always-loaded default in `smart_routing.md` |\n115: \n116: ---\n117: \n118: ## 6. RELATED RESOURCES\n119: \n120: ### Related Skills\n121: \n122: | Skill | Relationship | Use When |\n123: |---|---|---|\n124: | [`deep-improvement`](../../deep-improvement/SKILL.md) | Owns the Lane C benchmark harness | Running or extending the benchmark |\n125: | [`sk-code`](../SKILL.md) | The skill under measurement | Reading or tuning the router being scored |\n126: \n127: ### Related Documents\n128: \n129: | Document | Purpose |\n130: |---|---|\n\n(Showing lines 1-130 of 132. Use offset=131 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"sk-code Skill-Benchmark Artifacts\"\ndescription: \"Benchmark inputs and reports for sk-code, scored by the deep-improvement Lane C harness in router and live modes.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"sk-code benchmark\"\n  - \"skill-benchmark artifacts\"\n  - \"sk-code routing benchmark\"\n---\n\n# sk-code Skill-Benchmark Artifacts\n\n> Reports and inputs for benchmarking how well `sk-code` is routed, discovered, and used in practice, kept beside the skill they measure.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nThe deep-improvement Lane C harness benchmarks `sk-code` against its own `manual_testing_playbook` scenarios across five dimensions (D1 routing, D2 discovery, D3 efficiency, D4 usefulness, D5 connectivity). This folder holds the run inputs and the dual reports each run writes.\n\nTwo trace modes score the same playbook corpus:","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-code/benchmark/README.md","time":{"start":1780373659986,"end":1780373659994}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0931e497c333a5c6016a1e589be10c81918ef22e5ab1bdbed4"}},"id":"prt_e868a2150001OPtzknTdNO2oCR","sessionID":"ses_1797707a9ffehSuq7kNyovejK9","messageID":"msg_e868a01b7001DIxVjEKrMPaW73"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780373660000,"sessionID":"ses_1797707a9ffehSuq7kNyovejK9","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_JatAnvJn1EIiXGzYIoZorZBj","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/d5-connectivity.cjs","offset":1,"limit":240},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/d5-connectivity.cjs</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: #!/usr/bin/env node\n2: 'use strict';\n3: \n4: /**\n5:  * d5-connectivity.cjs — static structural scan, the D5 hard gate.\n6:  *\n7:  * Runs BEFORE any dispatch and caps the verdict regardless of weighted score.\n8:  * Catches the failure class that makes a skill structurally unusable: a\n9:  * RESOURCE_MAP path that does not exist (dead route), a RESOURCE_MAP key absent\n10:  * from INTENT_SIGNALS (dead intent key), a routed path escaping the skill root,\n11:  * and references present on disk but never reachable from any RESOURCE_MAP entry\n12:  * (orphans — reported, not gated). A router that cannot be parsed at all is the\n13:  * strongest gate failure.\n14:  */\n15: \n16: const fs = require('fs');\n17: const path = require('path');\n18: const { parseRouter } = require('./router-replay.cjs');\n19: \n20: function listMarkdownRefs(skillRoot) {\n21:   const out = [];\n22:   for (const dir of ['references', 'assets']) {\n23:     const base = path.join(skillRoot, dir);\n24:     if (!fs.existsSync(base)) continue;\n25:     const stack = [base];\n26:     while (stack.length) {\n27:       const cur = stack.pop();\n28:       for (const entry of fs.readdirSync(cur, { withFileTypes: true })) {\n29:         const full = path.join(cur, entry.name);\n30:         if (entry.isDirectory()) stack.push(full);\n31:         else if (entry.isFile() && /\\.md$/.test(entry.name)) out.push(path.relative(skillRoot, full));\n32:       }\n33:     }\n34:   }\n35:   return out;\n36: }\n37: \n38: /**\n39:  * @returns {{ score:number, gateFailed:boolean, findings:Array,\n40:  *   deadResourcePaths:string[], deadIntentKeys:string[], orphanReferences:string[],\n41:  *   pathEscapes:string[], routerParseable:boolean }}\n42:  */\n43: function scanConnectivity({ skillRoot }) {\n44:   const findings = [];\n45:   const skillMdPath = path.join(skillRoot, 'SKILL.md');\n46:   if (!fs.existsSync(skillMdPath)) {\n47:     // Score mirrors the normal penalty path (100 - one P0 of 40 = 60) so a\n48:     // score-comparison consumer sees the same number for the same one-P0\n49:     // condition; gateFailed is the authoritative verdict signal either way.\n50:     return {\n51:       score: 60, gateFailed: true, routerParseable: false,\n52:       deadResourcePaths: [], deadIntentKeys: [], orphanReferences: [], pathEscapes: [],\n53:       findings: [{ class: 'missing_skill_md', severity: 'P0', detail: 'SKILL.md not found' }],\n54:     };\n55:   }\n56:   const router = parseRouter(fs.readFileSync(skillMdPath, 'utf8'), skillRoot);\n57:   const intentKeys = new Set(Object.keys(router.intentSignals));\n58:   const deadResourcePaths = [];\n59:   const deadIntentKeys = [];\n60:   const pathEscapes = [];\n61:   const routedRefs = new Set();\n62:   // Always-loaded default resources are reachable on every route, so they count\n63:   // as covered (not orphans) even when no intent maps to them.\n64:   for (const r of router.defaultResource || []) routedRefs.add(r);\n65: \n66:   for (const [intent, resources] of Object.entries(router.resourceMap)) {\n67:     if (!intentKeys.has(intent)) {\n68:       deadIntentKeys.push(intent);\n69:       findings.push({ class: 'dead_intent_key', severity: 'P1', locus: `RESOURCE_MAP.${intent}`, detail: `${intent} has no INTENT_SIGNALS entry` });\n70:     }\n71:     for (const r of resources) {\n72:       routedRefs.add(r);\n73:       const root = path.resolve(skillRoot);\n74:       const resolved = path.resolve(skillRoot, r);\n75:       // Separator-bounded containment: a bare startsWith(root) would let a\n76:       // sibling like `<root>-evil/...` slip through as \"inside\" the skill root.\n77:       if (resolved !== root && !resolved.startsWith(root + path.sep)) {\n78:         pathEscapes.push(r);\n79:         findings.push({ class: 'path_escape', severity: 'P0', locus: r, detail: `${r} resolves outside skill root` });\n80:       } else if (!fs.existsSync(resolved)) {\n81:         deadResourcePaths.push(r);\n82:         findings.push({ class: 'dead_resource_path', severity: 'P0', locus: r, detail: `routed path ${r} does not exist` });\n83:       }\n84:     }\n85:   }\n86: \n87:   const orphanReferences = listMarkdownRefs(skillRoot).filter((ref) => !routedRefs.has(ref));\n88:   for (const orphan of orphanReferences) {\n89:     findings.push({ class: 'orphan_reference', severity: 'P2', locus: orphan, detail: `${orphan} is not reachable from any RESOURCE_MAP intent` });\n90:   }\n91: \n92:   // Hard gate: any P0 (dead path / escape / unparseable). Dead intent keys (P1)\n93:   // and orphans (P2) lower the score but do not gate by themselves.\n94:   const p0 = findings.filter((f) => f.severity === 'P0').length;\n95:   const gateFailed = p0 > 0 || !router.parseable;\n96:   if (!router.parseable) {\n97:     findings.push({ class: 'router_unparseable', severity: 'P0', detail: 'INTENT_SIGNALS / RESOURCE_MAP could not be parsed from SKILL.md' });\n98:   }\n99:   // Score: start at 100, subtract per finding by severity, floor 0.\n100:   const penalty = findings.reduce((acc, f) => acc + ({ P0: 40, P1: 12, P2: 3 }[f.severity] || 0), 0);\n101:   const score = Math.max(0, 100 - penalty);\n102: \n103:   return { score, gateFailed, routerParseable: router.parseable, deadResourcePaths, deadIntentKeys, orphanReferences, pathEscapes, findings };\n104: }\n105: \n106: module.exports = { scanConnectivity, listMarkdownRefs };\n107: \n108: if (require.main === module) {\n109:   const args = require('./_args.cjs').parse(process.argv.slice(2));\n110:   if (!args.skill) {\n111:     process.stderr.write('usage: d5-connectivity.cjs --skill <skill-root>\\n');\n112:     process.exit(2);\n113:   }\n114:   const res = scanConnectivity({ skillRoot: args.skill });\n115:   process.stdout.write(JSON.stringify(res, null, 2) + '\\n');\n116:   process.exit(res.gateFailed ? 1 : 0);\n117: }\n\n(End of file - total 117 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"#!/usr/bin/env node\n'use strict';\n\n/**\n * d5-connectivity.cjs — static structural scan, the D5 hard gate.\n *\n * Runs BEFORE any dispatch and caps the verdict regardless of weighted score.\n * Catches the failure class that makes a skill structurally unusable: a\n * RESOURCE_MAP path that does not exist (dead route), a RESOURCE_MAP key absent\n * from INTENT_SIGNALS (dead intent key), a routed path escaping the skill root,\n * and references present on disk but never reachable from any RESOURCE_MAP entry\n * (orphans — reported, not gated). A router that cannot be parsed at all is the\n * strongest gate failure.\n */\n\nconst fs = require('fs');\nconst path = require('path');\nconst { parseRouter } = require('./router-replay.cjs');\n\nfunction listMarkdownRefs(skillRoot) {","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/d5-connectivity.cjs","time":{"start":1780373659964,"end":1780373659995}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0931e497c333a5c6016a1e589be0e88191919d37e5a5cd6326"}},"id":"prt_e868a211d001jVNOQpNVrd2jHm","sessionID":"ses_1797707a9ffehSuq7kNyovejK9","messageID":"msg_e868a01b7001DIxVjEKrMPaW73"}}
